
[1]hoof-bound

   HOOF'-BOUND, a. A horse is said to be hoof-bound when he has a pain in
   the fore-feet, occasioned by the dryness and contraction of the horn of
   the quarters, which straightens the quarters of the heels,and often
   makes him lame.
